  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Joint Implementation Program for Support of the Humanitarian Response Plan in Yemen 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve access to basic education services for returnees, host communities and internally displaced persons (IDPs) in Aden, Lahj and Hadramout governorates (Yemen), which are facing some of the highest displacement and return rates in the country. By bringing host communities, IDPs and returnees together in cooperation with local government institutions, this initiative builds on previous interventions to enhance social cohesion within the communities and support the provision of education services and facilities in areas that were identified by the communities and authorities as most in need. This project targets eight schools in need of rehabilitation, reconstruction, furniture and equipment that have deteriorated following years of conflict. The project estimates to target a total of 4,500 students and 400 school staff.</narrative>
  </description>
